# 4. 最後の公演

Keisuke: Convincing the other executives was arduous, to put it mildly...
Keisuke: In any case, Wonderlands×Showtime has been cleared to become freelancers.
Keisuke: The discussion surrounding your troupe name did become a little heated, but we decided that you should be allowed to continue calling yourselves “Wonderlands×Showtime”...
Keisuke: Think of it as a small parting gift since we know this name means quite a lot to you...
Rui: Thank you very much.
Shosuke: So...
Shosuke: What did Emu say?
Rui: Emu said... She'll stay...
Shosuke: I see...
Keisuke: ...
Keisuke: Understood... Then, we'll start having contracts drafted up for the three of you...
Keisuke: We'll get them to you as soon as we can. You'll also need to go over them with your parents before you sign.
Rui: Thank you...
Keisuke: Now, about the near future.
Keisuke: The soonest we'll be able to release you from your current contracts is next month.
Keisuke: At the same time, the anniversary of Phoenix Wonderland's opening is coming up. Our plan is to put on a special show to mark the occasion.
Keisuke: So, we'd like to ask if you'd stay with the park until then...
Rui: For the park's anniversary...
Rui: Understood... I'll discuss this with the others.
Keisuke: Yes, please do.
Rui: Thank you both again for taking the time out of your busy schedules to meet with me. Now, if you'll excuse me...
Keisuke & Shosuke: ...
Rui: (I said I'd ask the others...)
Rui: (But it's a show to celebrate the park's anniversary. I'm sure they'll want to do it.)
Rui: (And if so... This will become the last show we put on together as the cast of the Wonder Stage...)
Rui: (Then, we should make it the best one we've ever done...)
Tsukasa: I see... A show to celebrate the park's anniversary.
Tsukasa: I mean, we can't say no, can we?
Nene: PXL's been really good to us, so we should return the favor.
Emu: Yeah...!
Rui: I had a feeling that you'd all want to do this. I'll let them know, then.
Miku: But...
Miku: Once this show's over, you three are gonna start performing in other places with other people, right...?
Miku: The four of you won't be doing shows together as much...
Rui: Yes, that's right...
Rui: Of course, it's not like we'll be leaving the Wonder Stage for good. I anticipate we'll receive opportunities to perform there again from time to time...
Rui: But it is true that it will no longer be our top priority since we'll be performing in shows with other troupes and such.
Rui: We may have to place them over the Wonder Stage if any scheduling conflicts arise.
Rui: We believe this is what we need to do to make our dreams come true...
Miku: Right...
Emu: Oh...
Emu: (What do I do...?)
Emu: (They've been given the chance to grow and learn and really go after their dreams...)
Emu: (But they seem really sad...)
Emu: (I can't leave things like this...)
Emu: (I wanna make it so we can all be smiling when we say goodbye to each other...!)
Emu: Alright! Let's make our next show the most fun one we've ever done!
Emu: So, for our last performance, we should put on that show...!
Tsukasa: That show...?
Emu: Yup!
Emu: The one we did with Miku and the others!
KAITO: One second. I have the script here somewhere...
KAITO: Ah, here we are. Hehe. It feels like we did this one such a long time ago.
Rui: “The Traveling Troupe”...
Rui: The one you all made for me. That takes me back...
Miku: Hehe. I still remember all my lines!
Miku: Once upon a time, there was an eccentric traveling theater troupe♪
Miku: The troupe consists of a show-offy troupe leader, a clown who won't listen, and a songstress who can't sing in public!
Miku: The oddball group staged many shows, but they never managed to attract an audience!
Miku: Then one day, as they were traveling through a forest, they encountered an alchemist who was performing a show all alone.
Miku: ...is how it starts, right♪
Rin: That's amazing, Miku☆ You still remember it all♪
Miku: Hehe. That's because it was the very first show I did with Emu and everyone! I remember my lines for the cute fairy too!
Emu: We should definitely do this one!
Emu: Because this is the super special show that let us become Wonderlands×Showtime!
Nene: Yeah, I agree...
Tsukasa: Yes. I also have no objections.
Tsukasa: Then... Starting tomorrow, we'll begin practicing it!
Emu: Yeah! Let's do it!
Emu: Oh nooo...!
Nene: Huh? What's wrong...?
Emu: I... I forgot where I put my script...!
Emu: I remember practicing with it in my room, but I also brought it over here to practice and... Here?! There?! Thataway?! No, wait...!
Tsukasa: Relax, I'm sure it'll...
Miku: Oh! I remember seeing your script in that big box over there, Emu!
Emu: What? Oh, that's right...! I left it there to make sure I wouldn't lose it!
Luka: Hehe. You forgot that you put it there?
Len: That's our Emu for you!
Emu: (Thank goodness... They don't look sad anymore.)
Emu: Anyway, bye, Miku! Bye, everyone! We hope you're looking forward to an amazing show!
Miku: Oh... Okay, bye!
Rui: ...
Miku: Huh? Rui, aren't you going back?
Rui: Oh, um... Yes... See you...
Miku: Rui didn't seem all that happy...
KAITO: Yes, I noticed...
KAITO: He must be feeling a little conflicted about doing that show, since it probably means the most to him. Also...
KAITO: It even ends with... “And they made shows together forever after.” So...
Len: Isn't there anything we can do for them...?
Rin: I also wanna help them if I can... But based on what they said, Emu's mind is already...
Luka: Yes... This is quite the predicament...
Miku: Then, does that mean there's nothing we can...?
MEIKO: No, I don't believe so.
Miku: Huh?
MEIKO: We're show performers, aren't we?
MEIKO: That means there's always something we can do for them!
Rin: Wait, are you saying...?
MEIKO: We should put on a show for them! One that'll make them smile and cheer them up a bit!
Miku: Yeah! That's a really great idea...!
KAITO: I agree...
KAITO: As the cast of this SEKAI, let's do what we can for them!
Len: So, what show are we gonna do? Any ideas for that?
MEIKO: Ah, I have the perfect one in mind!
MEIKO: We're going to do the same one as Emu and the others! “The Traveling Troupe”!
Luka: What? But the way it ends... KAITO just said how...
MEIKO: Yes, so...
MEIKO: Why don't we make it into a happy ending that's perfect for them...?
